Halve, then remove the core from the @green pepper{1} and chop into small pieces.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{1%drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat. When hot, add the @beef strips{240%g} and pepper and stir-fry until the beef is browned, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in the @smoked paprika{1%tsp} and @sugar{1%tsp} then pour in the @tomatoes{1}(finely chopped). Lower the heat to medium and simmer until thick and tomatoey, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Meanwhile, cook the @basmati rice{150%g} according to pack instructions.

Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1}(roughly chopped) (stalks and all). Stir half the parsley through the stew. Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

Serve the rice in #bowls{}. Swirl a spoonful of @soured cream{150%g} through the stew then serve on top of the rice. Finish with a dollop more of sour cream and a sprinkling of the remaining parsley.